title: Was Michigan-Michigan State finish more incredible than the Kick Six? Vote in our poll
text:
Practically everyone who witnessed the " Kick Six" at the end of the 2013 Iron Bowl figured it would never be topped.
But it's possible the ending of Saturday's Michigan-Michigan State game was as spectacular or even more so.
Consider the following:
• As with the Kick Six, it was a match-up of blood rivals, one of which was undefeated and both of which were in the thick of division and conference title races and national championship discussions.
• However, Michigan State was playing on the road and was trailing 23-21 in the closing seconds Saturday, only to pull off an incredible play for the win. In the 2013 Iron Bowl, Alabama and Auburn were tied 28-28 before the Tigers won on the Kick Six. Auburn was also the home team.
So which was more incredible? Vote in our poll below:
